    narr:narration """This hub gathers the roadmap, GTM, and document strategy for aswritten. Spine: the [strategy doc as single internal source of truth](narr:Narrative_DocumentEcosystem) from which nine audience-specific documents derive, and the [memory-to-worldview core product loop](narr:Narrative_CoreProductLoop). The near-term ship discipline lives in an [April-1 above-the-line list](narr:Claim_AboveTheLine_April1) (witnessed 20260320, revised 20260408) and a [three-blocker V1 scope](narr:Narrative_ThreeBlockers). GTM is framed several ways: a [[amount]–[amount] funding ladder](narr:Narrative_FundingLadder), an [expansion path](narr:Narrative_ExpansionPath), [three buyer-specific expansion tracks](narr:Narrative_ExpansionTracks), and [influence-first selling](narr:Narrative_InfluenceSales). A March SMB pivot reframes product ([GitHub abstraction](narr:Claim_GitHubAbstractionHighPriority) 20260312→20260319, [SMB module implications](narr:Obs_SMBProductImplications)). Product gaps name [onboarding/cognitive bootstrapping](narr:Claim_OnboardingModeHighestLeverage) as highest leverage, plus the [lens/layer parameter](narr:Claim_MissingCompileTimeLayerParameter) (20260414) and [topic-analysis as platform feature](narr:Claim_TopicAnalysisPlatformFeature) (20260501). a demo-call prospect and YC feedback drive [material priorities](narr:Obs_DemoProspectMaterialPriorities) and the [YC three-beat demo](narr:Decision_YCDemoBeats).""" ;
